        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 4:50PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 450 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Newland, or near B.R. Parkway-Linville Falls To Grandfather, moving
east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Newland, Banner Elk, Crossnore, Sugar Mountain, Seven Devils,
Grandfather Mountain State Park, B.R. Parkway-Linville Falls To
Grandfather, Edgemont, Pineola, and Linville.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
